author: Wesley Sinor | wsinor@al.com
title: Auburn's Xavier Dampeer 'doing OK' after reportedly injuring jaw in bar fight
text:
Xavier Dampeer's status remains unknown.
Auburn's second-string center reportedly injured his jaw Oct. 4 during a bar fight involving exiled receiver D'haquille Williams .
"He's doing OK," Auburn offensive coordinator Rhett Lashlee said Sunday night. "I don't know at this point (if he'll play this week.)"
Dampeer, has served as the backup to center Austin Golson this season. Lashlee said the Tigers have a plan in place if Dampeer isn't healthy enough for Thursday's game against Kentucky.
RELATED: Auburn 'never' discussed change at center
"We have several options we have kind of discussed throughout the summer, so we don't want to kind of divulge too much."
Alabama News Network reported Dampeer was treated and released from East Alabama Medical Center last week, according to a hospital worker. When contacted by AL.com, a hospital spokesperson said there was no patient record of Dampeer at the hospital.
